3. Christian Eriksen, QPR (PPI score: 51.1)

Eriksen helped his side to yet another late win on Sunday after his goal secured a 2-1 victory for Mauricio Pochettino's side. 

The Danish winger scored with his only shot on target at the Liberty Stadium while recording an 82 per cent pass completion rate.   

2. Eden Hazard, Chelsea (PPI score: 51.8) 

The diminutive Belgian continued his run of brilliant form in a blue shirt with a goal and an assist to help Chelsea to a 2-0 win against Hull. 

Hazard gave the Blues and early lead at Stamford Bridge with a well-time header, leaping to meet a superb cross from Oscar. The winger then set-up Diego Costa for his 12th Premier League goal of the season. 

1. Santi Cazorla, Arsenal (PPI score: 52.1)

Cazorla tops this week's chart following his brilliant double against Newcastle on Saturday evening. The Spaniard put his side into a 2-0 lead with a deft chip before rounding off the night with a delightful panenka penalty.  

